# TypeScript Standards — packages/sdk

- `strict: true` always. Never widen a type with `any` to make an error go
  away — fix the type instead.
- The RPC method/event maps (`RpcMethodMap`, `RpcEventMap`) are the single
  source of truth; every other type in this package should be derived from
  them (`keyof`, indexed access), not duplicated.
- Prefer discriminated unions over boolean flags for anything with more than
  two mutually-exclusive states (see `JsonRpcResponse` = success | error).
- Every exported function that can fail should reject/throw an `Error`
  instance with a descriptive message, never a bare string or object.
- No empty `catch` blocks. If you're intentionally swallowing an error, say
  why in a comment.
